<reply id="uk.org.publicwhip/wrans/2007-11-22a.92.5" speakerid="uk.org.publicwhip/lord/100015" speakername="Baroness Andrews" colon=":" colnum="92"  url="http://www.publications.parliament.uk/pa/ld200708/ldhansrd/text/71122w0002.htm#07112236000099">
	<p pid="a.92.5/1">Following the close of the public inquiry on <phrase class="date" code="2007-05-11">11 May</phrase> into the related appeals and orders for the Caythorpe gas storage proposal, an inspector's report has been submitted to the Secretaries of State for Communities and Local Government and for Business, Enterprise and Regulatory Reform. Decisions on the appeals and orders will be made by the relevant Secretary of State.</p>
	<p pid="a.92.5/2">This is a complex case requiring a number of joint decisions by both Secretaries of State, together with other decisions to be determined under a range of consent regimes. Although this planning case is not one with a set statutory timetable, this Government remain acutely aware of the need to ensure that decisions are taken as soon as possible.</p>
</reply>
